<paper id="1558349193"><title>An Overview of the CAPITL Software Development Environment</title><year>1995</year><authors><author org="Grammatech, Inc." id="2688592286">Paul Adams</author><author org="Computer Sciences Department" id="2143353419">Marvin H. Solomon</author></authors><n_citation>15</n_citation><doc_type /><references><reference>3295338</reference><reference>68886642</reference><reference>189454040</reference><reference>351767304</reference><reference>1970743412</reference><reference>1981832888</reference><reference>1988427440</reference><reference>1998723368</reference><reference>2007008666</reference><reference>2027240998</reference><reference>2033337919</reference><reference>2035182234</reference><reference>2054813151</reference><reference>2110631345</reference><reference>2112136855</reference><reference>2137606889</reference><reference>2142947709</reference><reference>2148238464</reference><reference>2157266926</reference><reference>2164306675</reference><reference>2166667085</reference><reference>2248224627</reference><reference>2296048500</reference></references><venue id="" type="">Selected papers from the ICSE SCM-4 and SCM-5 Workshops, on Software Configuration Management</venue><doi>10.1007/3-540-60578-9_1</doi><keywords><keyword weight="0.4757">Programming language</keyword><keyword weight="0.6094">Programming paradigm</keyword><keyword weight="0.61005">Data control language</keyword><keyword weight="0.4545">Computer science</keyword><keyword weight="0.61426">Fourth-generation programming language</keyword><keyword weight="0.62842">Interface description language</keyword><keyword weight="0.60419">High-level programming language</keyword><keyword weight="0.61188">Data manipulation language</keyword><keyword weight="0.60373">Low-level programming language</keyword><keyword weight="0.61948">Software development</keyword></keywords><publisher>Springer, Berlin, Heidelberg</publisher><abstract>The CAPITL programming environment is comprised of a shared, object-oriented, versioned database, an embedded logic-based data-manipulation language, and a graphical user interface. With each software object the database stores a rich set of attributes that describe its syntax, intended semantics, and relationship to other objects. CAPITL is implemented in POL, a data model and deductive query language with elements of persistent, object-oriented and logic-based programming languages. POL is implemented in and tightly coupled with C++.</abstract></paper>